## Server: Albert (100.95.7.96)

Project root is at `/workspace/{{ name }}/` (Web UI mode) or `/workspace/` (CLI mode).
Check with: `ls /workspace/` — if you see `{{ name }}/`, cd into it first.

⛔ **Never run a local dev server** (`manage.py runserver`, `flask run`, etc.). The local server has different env vars, no feature flags, and dies when the sandbox ends. The deployed app (URL printed by `deploy.py dev`) is the only valid test target.
⛔ **No synthetic test data.** Test with real user-provided files. Use `deploy.py logs dev` for tracebacks.
⛔ **Never test file uploads with curl.** Use `browser_upload_file` — curl bypasses the HTML form and hides field name mismatches.
⛔ **`localhost:5xxxx` ports in context are OpenHands internals** — not your app.
⛔ **Never background deploy.py** — the sandbox kills silent commands after 10s. Run it directly; it streams output throughout.

Deploy and verify:
```bash
cd /workspace/{{ name }} && python3 .ymir/deploy.py dev
python3 .ymir/deploy.py verify
# Errors? → python3 .ymir/deploy.py logs dev
```

## Reading and Writing Files

Use `execute_bash` to read and modify files:
```bash
cat /workspace/{{ name }}/views.py
```

⛔ **Never use `workspace_read`, `workspace_write`, or `workspace_run`** — these SSH back to the host and will time out.

## MCP Tools (browser + search only)

- `web_search(query)` — DuckDuckGo
- `web_fetch(url)` — fetch page as text
- `browser_visit(url)` / `browser_check_text(url, text)` / `browser_run_checks(url, checks)`
- `browser_upload_file(url, filename, b64)` / `browser_upload_and_check(url, filename, b64, texts)`

## Iterative TBD / BDD / TDD Cycle

Work in short, verifiable cycles — one failing test at a time:

1. **Reproduce** — confirm the bug with a real user file via `browser_upload_file` against the deployed URL. Never use synthetic data to reproduce.
2. **Branch** — `git checkout -b feat/<short-name>`
3. **Write a failing test first** — the test must fail before you write any implementation code. Commit it.
4. **Implement** — minimum code to make the test pass. Nothing more.
5. **All tests green** — run the full test suite; fix any regressions.
6. **Deploy dev** — `python3 .ymir/deploy.py dev`
7. **Verify with real data** — `browser_upload_file` (or `browser_upload_and_check`) against the deployed URL. This is the acceptance gate.
8. **If green** → merge to main, push, deploy prod.
9. **If red** → `git checkout main && git branch -D feat/<short-name>`. Document what failed. Start a new cycle with a different approach.

